itemLabel: William Beauclerk, 10th Duke of St Albans

wikipedia_page.main: William Amelius Aubrey de Vere Beauclerk, 10th Duke of St Albans, PC DL (15 April 1840 – 10 May 1898), styled Earl of Burford until 1849, was a British Liberal parliamentarian of the Victorian era.The Duke served in William Gladstone's government as Captain of the Yeomen of the Guard between 1868 and 1874.
